&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU’LL BE DOING &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Product &amp;amp; Solutions Manager is tasked with building new and localising &amp;amp; enhancing existing MiQ products &amp;amp; solutions for the China Outbound and MENA markets.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DELIVERING PRODUCT PORTFOLIO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all Products under your Portfolio are delivering against product objectives and market OKRs – as per set timelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Update timelines for Product &amp;amp; Solutions roadmap internally and externally periodically – based on pace set by VP Operations, Emerging Markets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ideate and contribute to product localisation for the China Outbound market – including training, localisation of collateral (in collaboration with Marketing)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cross-functional collaboration with product, marketing, sales, trading, account management and CoE teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relentlessly pursues adoption of best practices in product management across different work streams, continuously evaluates how teams are operating and ensures consistency &amp;amp; timely project delivery&lt;/li&gt;
